commitResults.messageTitle: Modified Greetings, added Echo feature and Exit feature
Added ability to store text input from user
Added ability to display stored user inputs
Customized some of Duke's outputs
Added Task Class and ability to mark Task as done
Added Event, Deadline and Todo class inherited from Task, suppoorts tracking for 3 task types
Added Semi-Automatic Testing
Moditified printList to handle empty list prints
Added DukeException class to handle error in user input
Added function to delete tasks from list. Also modified list to be ArrayList and removed counter for list. Updated semi-automatic test cases.
Replaces "\t" with 4 spaces
commitResults.messageBody:
As part of customization, tab was used instead of simply spaces.

Not all computer's tab spaces are the same.

Let's replace tab spaces with 4 spaces in the strings 
to produce similar UI visuals for Duke.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adds Save function
commitResults.messageBody:
Part of the project requirements.


Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically 
whenever the task list changes. 

Load the data from the hard disk when Duke starts up.

Data loaded in from "/data/duke.txt".
May not be OS independent.

Loading of data is not equipped to handle data not in
specific format.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adds Date recognition for Deadline Tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Part of Project Requirements (Level-8).

Takes in dates for Deadline within strings in the 
format of "yyyy-mm-dd" and displays it as "dd MMM yyyy".

Some code was added to Event class to prepare for
future modifications that will allow Duke to recognize
both Date and Time within the command string of an
Event Task.

commitResults.messageTitle: Updates loadFileContents() method to include Level-8 additions
commitResults.messageBody:
Save function was done without taking into account
the changes made to let Deadline tasks recognize their
string inputs as dates. Since loadFileContents() method
lets Duke load old data, the method needed to be 
updated to properly recognize dates from the saved
data file (if any).

Also updates some comments so that they are no 
longer inaccurate.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adds 5 classes to improve OOP and refactor the code
commitResults.messageBody:
Part of A-MoreOOP requirements.

Refactors the code to extract out closely related code as classes.

Adds the following classes,
- Ui: deals with interactions with the user
- Storage: deals with loading tasks from the file and saving tasks in the file
- Parser: deals with making sense of the user command
- TaskList: contains the task list e.g., it has operations to add/delete tasks in the list
- Command: enum class to denote commands parsed by the Parser

Commit is untested. May require more edits before pushing.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fixes minor bugs from last commit
commitResults.messageBody:
The previous commit adds 5 new classes to improve OOP and
also refactors the code a little. The commit did not undergo testing.

Several testing was done and fixes were made based off
the test results.

The following are some of the fixes made:
- Adjusted some UI element to be more uniform.
- Fixed TaskList deleteTask() and markTaskDone() methods
  to perform correct actions on the right index. Also changed
  the exception catching to catch IndexOutOfBoundsException
  instead of ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adds a few JUnit tests for Parser and TaskList
commitResults.messageBody:
For project requirement A-JUnit.

Adds several JUnit test methods for Duke,
- Adds a dummy test method in DukeTest class.
- Adds a few test methods in ParserTest that checks 
  invalid command, valid Todo commands, valid and 
  invalid Deadline commands.
- Adds test methods in TaskListTest to that tests invalid index 
  error when using the 'done' command.
